The Oklahoma State mens team placed first in the Cowboy Jamboree on Saturday PERIOD

The No PERIOD  mens No PERIOD  womens Oklahoma State cross country teams finished second and first respectively at this years Big  championships in Waco Texas PERIOD

For the Cowgirls this is the second conference title in program history while there Cowboys finish as runnersup for the second year in a row PERIOD

Taylor Somers finished second posting a . for the fourthfastest 6K in school history PERIOD Finishing one spot behind Somers was fellow Cowgirl Molly Born finishing . pERIOD

The pair was joined by Keytlyn Larson who finished twelfth with a . on the AllBig  team PERIOD

For the Cowboys Isai Rodriguez was the runnerup in the mens 8K PERIOD Behind Rodriguez in third place was Ryan Smeeton who was making his season debut PERIOD

Bryce Quigley was the third and final member of the Cowboys to make the AllBig  team finishing fourteenth PERIOD
